#: ui/pages/data_page.py:378
msgid ""
"Copy samples from source subdirectories into class folders under the raw data root. Skip this tab if your data is "
"already organized as one folder per class."
msgstr ""

#: ui/pages/data_page.py:382
msgid ""
"Normalize images to JPEG under each class’s CONVERTED/ folder. Point Raw data dir at the same tree on an internal or "
"external drive; outputs stay beside sources."
msgstr ""

#: ui/pages/data_page.py:386
msgid "Remove duplicates and quarantine very small images (by pixel size) to small_images_review/ under the raw root."
msgstr ""

#: ui/pages/data_page.py:389
msgid ""
"Upscale images previously moved to the small-image review area (after deduplicate). Default review dir is "
"raw_data/small_images_review when left empty."
msgstr ""

#: ui/pages/data_page.py:393
msgid ""
"Build train/ and test/ under the output data directory from the raw tree. A good place to put the final dataset on "
"your main drive while raw data stays external."
msgstr ""

#: ui/pages/data_page.py:412
msgid ""
"Gather copies files into timestamped runs under the target dir and tracks hashes so reruns skip already-seen files. "
"Set raw data dir to the pipeline root used by later steps."
msgstr ""

#: ui/pages/data_page.py:416
msgid ""
"Convert walks class folders, writes CONVERTED/ JPEGs, and records a unified snapshot. For image classification, "
"videos and multi-frame GIFs may yield a random frame JPEG. Very large images are downscaled (max edge 4000px)."
msgstr ""

#: ui/pages/data_page.py:421
msgid ""
"Deduplicate removes duplicate images and handles tiny dimensions: removes very small images and moves borderline-"
"small ones to small_images_review/ for manual review before upscale."
msgstr ""

#: ui/pages/data_page.py:425
msgid "Upscale processes the review tree produced by deduplicate for undersized images you choose to keep."
msgstr ""

#: ui/pages/data_page.py:428
msgid ""
"Create-dataset reads from raw data (including CONVERTED/) and writes the train/test split to the output data dir. Set"
" output on a spacious internal disk if raw data lives on external storage."
msgstr ""

#: ui/pages/data_page.py:443
msgid ""
"Storage: convert reads and writes under the raw data path you choose (including on removable drives). Create Dataset "
"copies into the output data directory—often set that to your main disk. Large images: convert downscales long edges; "
"tiny images: deduplicate moves small files to small_images_review/. Full discussion: docs/DATA_PIPELINE.md."
msgstr ""

